# 🌐 Useful Security Resources  

Here are some amazing websites that can help with Web, API, Network, and Mobile security research.  

---

## 🔹 **Web Security Resources**  
| Website | Description |
|---------|------------|
| [Web Security Academy](https://portswigger.net/web-security) | Free training by Burp Suite (SQLi, XSS, SSRF, etc.) |
| [PayloadsAllTheThings](https://github.com/swisskyrepo/PayloadsAllTheThings) | Collection of pentesting payloads |
| [XSS Payloads](https://xsshunter.com/) | Automated XSS payload testing |
| [Bug Bounty Notes](https://www.bugbountynotes.com/) | Tips, payloads, and bug bounty methodologies |

---

## 🔹 **API Security Resources**  
| Website | Description |
|---------|------------|
| [API Security Academy](https://portswigger.net/web-security/api-security) | Free API pentesting course |
| [GraphQL Security](https://lab.wallarm.com/graphql-security-complete-guide/) | Guide to testing GraphQL APIs |
| [SecLists API Wordlists](https://github.com/danielmiessler/SecLists) | API fuzzing wordlists |

---

## 🔹 **Network Security Resources**  
| Website | Description |
|---------|------------|
| [Nmap Cheat Sheet](https://highon.coffee/blog/nmap-cheat-sheet/) | Common Nmap scanning commands |
| [Wireshark Labs](https://wiki.wireshark.org/SampleCaptures) | Sample PCAP files for network analysis |
| [Metasploit Unleashed](https://www.offensive-security.com/metasploit-unleashed/) | Free Metasploit training |

---

## 🔹 **Mobile Security Resources**  
| Website | Description |
|---------|------------|
| [Android Security Guide](https://mobile-security.gitbook.io/mobile-security-testing-guide/) | Mobile Security Testing Guide |
| [iOS App Security](https://owasp.org/www-project-ios-security/) | OWASP iOS Security Project |
| [Frida & Objection](https://github.com/nowsecure/objection) | Runtime mobile app analysis |

---

### **📌 How to Use This?**  
- Visit these websites to **learn, practice, and improve your skills**  
- Add new sites as you discover them  

